NAME
    Data::Dump::ObjectAsString - Like Data::Dump but objects are stringified
    instead of dumped

VERSION
    This document describes version 0.001 of Data::Dump::ObjectAsString
    (from Perl distribution Data-Dump-ObjectAsString), released on
    2020-06-04.

SYNOPSIS
    Use like you would use Data::Dump:

     use Data::Dump::ObjectAsString;
     dd [1,2,3,4];

DESCRIPTION
    This is actually a thin wrapper of Data::Dump::Options. When dumping,
    $Data::Dump::Options::OBJECT_AS is locally set to "string".

HOMEPAGE
    Please visit the project's homepage at
    <https://metacpan.org/release/Data-Dump-ObjectAsString>.

SOURCE
    Source repository is at
    <https://github.com/perlancar/perl-Data-Dump-ObjectAsString>.

